@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(STM-CYCLE-LIFECYCLE, 0001)
' @id(STM-CYCLE-LIFECYCLE)
' @ref(DOM-CYCLE)
'
' Current-side lifecycle as implemented: cycle::CycleStatus is
' { Open, Closed, Aborted }; transitions are driven by the /mdd-cycle
' skill. The clarification pause is enforced by the skill but is not a
' persisted status, so it is shown as a self-transition on Open.
'
' @desc(STM-CYCLE-LIFECYCLE, "As-built Cycle lifecycle: CycleStatus Open->Closed on /mdd-review parity (after snapshot + diff written), or Open->Aborted on user cancel.")
title Cycle lifecycle (current)

[*] --> Open : /mdd-cycle opens cycle\n(manifest status: open, before/ snapshot)

state Open {
  [*] --> Looping
  Looping --> Looping : implement -> map ->\nvalidate -> review (mismatch)
  Looping --> AwaitingClarification : ambiguous decision
  AwaitingClarification --> Looping : user answers
}

Open --> Closed : /mdd-review parity matches\n(after/ snapshot + <diagram>.diff.puml)
Open --> Aborted : user cancels the run

Closed --> [*]
Aborted --> [*]

note right of Open
  before/ captured at open. The
  AwaitingClarification step is enforced by
  SKILL.md (never guess) but is not a
  CycleStatus variant in code.
end note

note right of Closed
  manifest: status=closed, closed_at set,
  touched_files populated. .mdd/cycles/<N>/
  now has before/, after/, and the annotated
  diff the viewer renders.
end note
@enduml
